cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network for automatic MRI cardiac segmentation, which is a computer vision task (cs.CV). The network is designed to learn both high-level and low-level features, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a multi-resolution conv-deconv architecture, which is commonly used in medical image analysis (cs.MM). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a loss function tailored to the cardiac anatomy, which suggests the use of optimization techniques such as neural networks (cs.NE).
